<div>
<p>Hi <%= @person.first_name %>,</p>

<p>Election Day was yesterday, so we now have a reprieve from endless ads in our mailboxes — at least until October. Let’s celebrate with a Julie Loyd house concert!</p>

<ul class="summary">
<li><%= @show.name %></li>
<li><%= @show.start_date %> &middot; <%= @show.start_time %></li>
<li><%= @show.venue.location %></li>
<li>RSVP for location/directions</li>
</ul>

<p class="actions"><strong>
<%= link_to "Yes! I’m in for #{@show.name}!", @rsvp_url_yes, class: 'button', style: 'background-color: #408000; color: white; padding: 5px 10px; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; margin-top: 5px; border-radius: 3px;' %>
<%= link_to "Sorry, I can’t make it", @rsvp_url_no, class: 'button', style: 'background-color: #444; color: white; padding: 5px 10px; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; margin-top: 5px; border-radius: 3px;' %>
</strong></p>

<h2>A bit about <%= @show.name %></h2>
<p>Now more than old enough to rent her own cars, and with even more letters after her name, I’m excited to have Julie Loyd back.</p>

<p>Julie is an award-winning songwriter toting along her banjo, guitar and heart-thumping, lyric-driven songs. Characterized by <cite>Curve</cite> magazine as “a charming acoustic spitfire,” Loyd is a seasoned performer with 20 years of experience on stage.</p>

<p>A child of musical theater, Julie has released six solo albums — some folk-pop, some indie-pop and even one she calls indie-grass (which is not something you can smoke).</p>

<p><%= link_to "Spend #{@show.day_of_week} evening with #{@show.name}", @rsvp_url_yes %>.</p>

<p><br/>Paul</p>

<p>P.S. If you have moved or don’t want to receive house concert invites, <%= link_to "instantly unsubscribe", @unsub_url %>.</p>

</div>
